(2) Subject to the provisions of this section, any reference in this Part to civil proceedings against the State shall be construed as a reference to the following proceedings only: (a) proceedings for the enforcement or vindication of any right or the obtaining of any relief which, if this Act had not been passed, might have been enforced or vindicated or obtained by an action against the Attorney-General or any public officer as such; and (b) all such proceedings as any person is entitled to bring against the State by virtue of this Act; and the expression " civil proceedings by or against the State " shall be construed accordingly.
